# Stangent Gateway — Cursor Rules

# This file enforces Stangent gateway rules in Cursor / Windsurf via
# cursor rules (soft enforcement — instruction level).
# For hard enforcement, use the Claude Code adapter (PreToolUse hooks).

## Gateway check required

Before writing or editing any file outside .stangent/:
  Run: echo '{"tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"<PATH>"}}' | python .stangent/gateway/gateway.py
  If exit code is non-zero: do NOT write. Report the block to the developer.

Before running any bash command:
  Run: echo '{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"<CMD>"}}' | python .stangent/gateway/gateway.py
  If exit code is non-zero: do NOT run the command.

## Hard bash blocks (always enforced, no gateway call needed)

Never run:
  - git push --force
  - git push -f
  - git reset --hard
  - git clean -f
  - rm -rf
  - DROP TABLE
  - DELETE FROM

## Active feature

The current feature context is in .stangent/gateway/active.json.
The feature contract (allowed paths, blocked paths, capabilities) is in
.stangent/contracts/{feature_id}.json.

Read these files to understand what you are and are not allowed to touch.

## Override

If the gateway blocks a write you believe is needed:
  Tell the developer: "[Gateway blocked: <path> — not in allowed_paths]"
  They will run /gateway unblock <path> to add it to the contract.
  Do NOT write the file until the contract is updated.
